# get the array of an image patch. default size (96, 96, 3)

def get_patch(file_path, start_position=[0, 0], dimension=[96, 96], level=0):
    
    """
    function to show a patch from an image
    
    Args:
        file_path: directory of image file
        start_position: x andy coordinates of starting position to show
        dimension: dimension of the patch to show
        level: level of image (0 is the highest definition level)
    Return:
        a image patch.
    """
    
    reader = mir.MultiResolutionImageReader()
    mr_image = reader.open(file_path)
    image_patch = mr_image.getUCharPatch(start_position[0], start_position[1], dimension[0], dimension[1], level)
    
    return image_patch

def annotateImage(input_file_name, camelyon17=True):
    
    """
    function to convert an annotation to an indexed mask iamge
    
    Args:
        input_file_name: name of input image file for conversion
        camelyon17: True if the image is from camelyon17 dataset, otherwise False
    Return:
        None
    """
    
    if camelyon17:
        camelyon_path = 'C17/'
        patient_path = input_file_name[:11]
        input_image_path = ''.join([camelyon_path, 'tif/', patient_path, '/', input_file_name, '.tif'])
    else:
        camelyon_path = 'C16/'
        input_image_path = ''.join([camelyon_path, 'tif/', input_file_name, '.tif'])
        
    input_annotation_path = ''.join([camelyon_path, 'xml/', input_file_name, '.xml'])
    output_image_path = ''.join([camelyon_path, 'tif_labels/', input_file_name, '_labels.tif'])
    
    reader = mir.MultiResolutionImageReader()
    mr_image = reader.open(input_image_path)
    
    annotation_list = mir.AnnotationList()
    annotation_list = mir.AnnotationList()
    xml_repository = mir.XmlRepository(annotation_list)
    xml_repository.setSource(input_annotation_path)
    xml_repository.load()
    
    annotation_mask = mir.AnnotationToMask()
    
    label_map = {'metastases': 1, 'normal': 2} if camelyon17 else {'_0': 1, '_1': 1, '_2': 0}
    conversion_order = ['metastases', 'normal'] if camelyon17 else  ['_0', '_1', '_2'] 
    
    annotation_mask.convert(annotation_list, output_image_path, mr_image.getDimensions(), mr_image.getSpacing(), label_map, conversion_order)

class binarySmallerVGGNet:
    @staticmethod
    def build():
        
        """
        width : The image width dimension.
        height : The image height dimension.
        depth : The depth of the image  also known as the number of channels.
        classes : The number of classes in our dataset (which will affect the last layer of our model). 
        """
        
        
        # initialize the model along with the input shape to be
        # "channels last" and the channels dimension itself
        model = Sequential()
        inputShape = (96, 96, 3)
        chanDim = -1

        # if we are using "channels first", update the input shape
        # and channels dimension
        if K.image_data_format() == "channels_first":
            inputShape = (depth, height, width)
            chanDim = 1
            
        # CONV => RELU => POOL
        model.add(Conv2D(32, (3, 3), padding="same",
        input_shape=inputShape))
        model.add(Activation("relu"))
        model.add(BatchNormalization(axis=chanDim))
        model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(3, 3)))
        model.add(Dropout(0.25))
    
        # (CONV => RELU) * 2 => POOL
        model.add(Conv2D(64, (3, 3), padding="same"))
        model.add(Activation("relu"))
        model.add(BatchNormalization(axis=chanDim))
        model.add(Conv2D(64, (3, 3), padding="same"))
        model.add(Activation("relu"))
        model.add(BatchNormalization(axis=chanDim))
        model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
        model.add(Dropout(0.25))
        
        # (CONV => RELU) * 2 => POOL
        model.add(Conv2D(128, (3, 3), padding="same"))
        model.add(Activation("relu"))
        model.add(BatchNormalization(axis=chanDim))
        model.add(Conv2D(128, (3, 3), padding="same"))
        model.add(Activation("relu"))
        model.add(BatchNormalization(axis=chanDim))
        model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
        model.add(Dropout(0.25))

        # return the constructed network architecture
        return model

'''
ResNet50 model for Keras.
# Reference:
- from https://github.com/fchollet/deep-learning-models/blob/master/resnet50.py
- [Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition](https://arxiv.org/abs/1512.03385)
Adapted from code contributed by BigMoyan.
'''

WEIGHTS_PATH = 'https://github.com/fchollet/deep-learning-models/releases/download/v0.2/resnet50_weights_tf_dim_ordering_tf_kernels.h5'
WEIGHTS_PATH_NO_TOP = 'https://github.com/fchollet/deep-learning-models/releases/download/v0.2/resnet50_weights_tf_dim_ordering_tf_kernels_notop.h5'


def identity_block(input_tensor, kernel_size, filters, stage, block):
    """The identity block is the block that has no conv layer at shortcut.
    # Arguments
        input_tensor: input tensor
        kernel_size: defualt 3, the kernel size of middle conv layer at main path
        filters: list of integers, the filterss of 3 conv layer at main path
        stage: integer, current stage label, used for generating layer names
        block: 'a','b'..., current block label, used for generating layer names
    # Returns
        Output tensor for the block.
    """
    filters1, filters2, filters3 = filters
    if K.image_data_format() == 'channels_last':
        bn_axis = 3
    else:
        bn_axis = 1
    conv_name_base = 'res' + str(stage) + block + '_branch'
    bn_name_base = 'bn' + str(stage) + block + '_branch'

    x = Conv2D(filters1, (1, 1), name=conv_name_base + '2a')(input_tensor)
    x = BatchNormalization(axis=bn_axis, name=bn_name_base + '2a')(x)
    x = Activation('relu')(x)

    x = Conv2D(filters2, kernel_size,
               padding='same', name=conv_name_base + '2b')(x)
    x = BatchNormalization(axis=bn_axis, name=bn_name_base + '2b')(x)
    x = Activation('relu')(x)

    x = Conv2D(filters3, (1, 1), name=conv_name_base + '2c')(x)
    x = BatchNormalization(axis=bn_axis, name=bn_name_base + '2c')(x)

    x = layers.add([x, input_tensor])
    x = Activation('relu')(x)
    return x


def conv_block(input_tensor, kernel_size, filters, stage, block, strides=(2, 2)):
    """conv_block is the block that has a conv layer at shortcut
    # Arguments
        input_tensor: input tensor
        kernel_size: defualt 3, the kernel size of middle conv layer at main path
        filters: list of integers, the filterss of 3 conv layer at main path
        stage: integer, current stage label, used for generating layer names
        block: 'a','b'..., current block label, used for generating layer names
    # Returns
        Output tensor for the block.
    Note that from stage 3, the first conv layer at main path is with strides=(2,2)
    And the shortcut should have strides=(2,2) as well
    """
    
    
    filters1, filters2, filters3 = filters
    if K.image_data_format() == 'channels_last':
        bn_axis = 3
    else:
        bn_axis = 1
    conv_name_base = 'res' + str(stage) + block + '_branch'
    bn_name_base = 'bn' + str(stage) + block + '_branch'

    x = Conv2D(filters1, (1, 1), strides=strides,
               name=conv_name_base + '2a')(input_tensor)
    x = BatchNormalization(axis=bn_axis, name=bn_name_base + '2a')(x)
    x = Activation('relu')(x)

    x = Conv2D(filters2, kernel_size, padding='same',
               name=conv_name_base + '2b')(x)
    x = BatchNormalization(axis=bn_axis, name=bn_name_base + '2b')(x)
    x = Activation('relu')(x)

    x = Conv2D(filters3, (1, 1), name=conv_name_base + '2c')(x)
    x = BatchNormalization(axis=bn_axis, name=bn_name_base + '2c')(x)

    shortcut = Conv2D(filters3, (1, 1), strides=strides,
                      name=conv_name_base + '1')(input_tensor)
    shortcut = BatchNormalization(axis=bn_axis, name=bn_name_base + '1')(shortcut)

    x = layers.add([x, shortcut])
    x = Activation('relu')(x)
    return x


def ResNet50(include_top=True, weights=None,
             input_tensor=None, input_shape=None,
             pooling=None,
             classes=1000):
    """Instantiates the ResNet50 architecture.
    Optionally loads weights pre-trained
    on ImageNet. Note that when using TensorFlow,
    for best performance you should set
    `image_data_format="channels_last"` in your Keras config
    at ~/.keras/keras.json.
    The model and the weights are compatible with both
    TensorFlow and Theano. The data format
    convention used by the model is the one
    specified in your Keras config file.
    # Arguments
        include_top: whether to include the fully-connected
            layer at the top of the network.
        weights: one of `None` (random initialization)
            or "imagenet" (pre-training on ImageNet).
        input_tensor: optional Keras tensor (i.e. output of `layers.Input()`)
            to use as image input for the model.
        input_shape: optional shape tuple, only to be specified
            if `include_top` is False (otherwise the input shape
            has to be `(224, 224, 3)` (with `channels_last` data format)
            or `(3, 224, 244)` (with `channels_first` data format).
            It should have exactly 3 inputs channels,
            and width and height should be no smaller than 197.
            E.g. `(200, 200, 3)` would be one valid value.
        pooling: Optional pooling mode for feature extraction
            when `include_top` is `False`.
            - `None` means that the output of the model will be
                the 4D tensor output of the
                last convolutional layer.
            - `avg` means that global average pooling
                will be applied to the output of the
                last convolutional layer, and thus
                the output of the model will be a 2D tensor.
            - `max` means that global max pooling will
                be applied.
        classes: optional number of classes to classify images
            into, only to be specified if `include_top` is True, and
            if no `weights` argument is specified.
    # Returns
        A Keras model instance.
    # Raises
        ValueError: in case of invalid argument for `weights`,
            or invalid input shape.
    """
    from tensorflow.keras import backend as k
    
    if weights not in {'imagenet', None}:
        raise ValueError('The `weights` argument should be either '
                         '`None` (random initialization) or `imagenet` '
                         '(pre-training on ImageNet).')

    if weights == 'imagenet' and include_top and classes != 1000:
        raise ValueError('If using `weights` as imagenet with `include_top`'
                         ' as true, `classes` should be 1000')

    # Determine proper input shape
    input_shape = _obtain_input_shape(input_shape,
                                      default_size=224,
                                      min_size=197,
                                      data_format=K.image_data_format(),
                                      require_flatten=include_top)

    if input_tensor is None:
        img_input = Input(shape=input_shape)
    else:
        if not K.is_keras_tensor(input_tensor):
            img_input = Input(tensor=input_tensor, shape=input_shape)
        else:
            img_input = input_tensor
            
    if K.image_data_format() == 'channels_last':
        bn_axis = 3
    else:
        bn_axis = 1

    x = ZeroPadding2D((3, 3))(img_input)
    x = Conv2D(64, (3, 3), strides=(2, 2), name='conv1')(x)  # conv window changed from (7, 7) to (3, 3) to avoid negative numbers
    x = BatchNormalization(axis=bn_axis, name='bn_conv1')(x)
    x = Activation('relu')(x)
    x = MaxPooling2D((3, 3), strides=(2, 2))(x)

    x = conv_block(x, 3, [64, 64, 256], stage=2, block='a', strides=(1, 1))
    x = identity_block(x, 3, [64, 64, 256], stage=2, block='b')
    x = identity_block(x, 3, [64, 64, 256], stage=2, block='c')

    x = conv_block(x, 3, [128, 128, 512], stage=3, block='a')
    x = identity_block(x, 3, [128, 128, 512], stage=3, block='b')
    x = identity_block(x, 3, [128, 128, 512], stage=3, block='c')
    x = identity_block(x, 3, [128, 128, 512], stage=3, block='d')

    x = conv_block(x, 3, [256, 256, 1024], stage=4, block='a')
    x = identity_block(x, 3, [256, 256, 1024], stage=4, block='b')
    x = identity_block(x, 3, [256, 256, 1024], stage=4, block='c')
    x = identity_block(x, 3, [256, 256, 1024], stage=4, block='d')
    x = identity_block(x, 3, [256, 256, 1024], stage=4, block='e')
    x = identity_block(x, 3, [256, 256, 1024], stage=4, block='f')

    x = conv_block(x, 3, [512, 512, 2048], stage=5, block='a')
    x = identity_block(x, 3, [512, 512, 2048], stage=5, block='b')
    x = identity_block(x, 3, [512, 512, 2048], stage=5, block='c')

    x = AveragePooling2D((3, 3), name='avg_pool')(x)

    if include_top:
        x = Flatten()(x)
        x = Dense(classes, activation='softmax', name='fc1000')(x)
    else:
        if pooling == 'avg':
            x = GlobalAveragePooling2D()(x)
        elif pooling == 'max':
            x = GlobalMaxPooling2D()(x)

    # Ensure that the model takes into account
    # any potential predecessors of `input_tensor`.
    if input_tensor is not None:
        inputs = get_source_inputs(input_tensor)
    else:
        inputs = img_input
    # Create model.
    model = Model(inputs, x, name='resnet50')

    # load weights
    if weights == 'imagenet':
        if include_top:
            weights_path = get_file('resnet50_weights_tf_dim_ordering_tf_kernels.h5',
                                    WEIGHTS_PATH,
                                    cache_subdir='models',
                                    md5_hash='a7b3fe01876f51b976af0dea6bc144eb')
        else:
            weights_path = get_file('resnet50_weights_tf_dim_ordering_tf_kernels_notop.h5',
                                    WEIGHTS_PATH_NO_TOP,
                                    cache_subdir='models',
                                    md5_hash='a268eb855778b3df3c7506639542a6af')
        model.load_weights(weights_path)
        if K.backend() == 'theano':
            layer_utils.convert_all_kernels_in_model(model)

        if K.image_data_format() == 'channels_first':
            if include_top:
                maxpool = model.get_layer(name='avg_pool')
                shape = maxpool.output_shape[1:]
                dense = model.get_layer(name='fc1000')
                layer_utils.convert_dense_weights_data_format(dense, shape, 'channels_first')

            if K.backend() == 'tensorflow':
                warnings.warn('You are using the TensorFlow backend, yet you '
                              'are using the Theano '
                              'image data format convention '
                              '(`image_data_format="channels_first"`). '
                              'For best performance, set '
                              '`image_data_format="channels_last"` in '
                              'your Keras config '
                              'at ~/.keras/keras.json.')
    return model

# custom auc_roc calculation for keras monitor
# https://stackoverflow.com/questions/43263111/defining-an-auc-metric-for-keras-to-support-evaluation-of-validation-dataset

def auc_roc(y_true, y_pred, tf_2=False):
    """
    Args:
        y_true: true y labels array (0 or 1);
        y_pred: predicted y label array (0 or 1);
    
    Return:
        auc_roc.
    """
    if tf_2:
        score = tf.py_function( lambda y_true, y_pred : roc_auc_score( y_true, y_pred, average='macro', sample_weight=None).astype('float32'),
                    [y_true, y_pred],
                    'float32',
                    stateful=False,
                    name='sklearnAUC' )
    else:
        score = tf.py_func( lambda y_true, y_pred : roc_auc_score( y_true, y_pred, average='macro', sample_weight=None).astype('float32'),
                    [y_true, y_pred],
                    'float32',
                    stateful=False,
                    name='sklearnAUC' )
    
    
    return score

# from https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41032551/how-to-compute-receiving-operating-characteristic-roc-and-auc-in-keras

class auc_roc_callback(tf.keras.callbacks.Callback):   
    def __init__(self,training_data,validation_data):
        self.x = training_data[0]
        self.y = training_data[1]
        self.x_val = validation_data[0]
        self.y_val = validation_data[1]

    def on_train_begin(self, logs={}):
        return

    def on_train_end(self, logs={}):
        return

    def on_epoch_begin(self, epoch, logs={}):
        return

    def on_epoch_end(self, epoch, logs={}):
        y_pred = self.model.predict_proba(self.x, verbose=0)
        auc = roc_auc_score(self.y, y_pred)
        logs['auc_roc'] = auc

        y_pred_val = self.model.predict_proba(self.x_val, verbose=0)
        val_auc = roc_auc_score(self.y_val, y_pred_val)
        logs['val_auc_roc'] = val_auc
        
        print('\auc_roc: {} - val_auc_roc: {}' % (auc, val_auc))
        return

    def on_batch_begin(self, batch, logs={}):
        return

    def on_batch_end(self, batch, logs={}):
        return

# custom callback for logging train loss, train auc, train accuracy, valid loss, valid auc and valid accuracy.

class LossHistory(tf.keras.callbacks.Callback):
    def on_train_begin(self, logs={}):
        self.losses = []
        self.accuracy = []
        self.auc_roc = []
        self.val_loss = []
        self.val_accuracy = []
        self.val_auc_roc = []

    def on_batch_end(self, batch, logs={}):
        self.losses.append(logs.get('loss'))
        self.accuracy.append(logs.get('accuracy'))
        self.auc_roc.append(logs.get('auc_roc'))
        self.val_loss.append(logs.get('val_loss'))
        self.val_accuracy.append(logs.get('val_accuracy'))
        self.val_auc_roc.append(logs.get('val_auc_roc'))

# function to train CNN model

def train_cnn_models(model, x_train, y_train, x_valid, y_valid, save_model_path, epochs=20, init_lr=1e-5, batch_size=32, 
                     frozen=False, subsets=False):
    """
    Args:
        model: model name. can be chosen from 'InceptionResNetV2', 'Xception', 'DenseNet', 'NASNet', 'InceptionV3',
               'ResNet50', 'small VGGNet' and 'small CNN';
        save_model_path: path to save trained model;
        epochs: no of epochs;
        init_lr: initil learning rate;
        batch_size: minibatch size;
        subsets: True if divide the train sample into 27 subsets with 10K samples each.
    Return:
        H: a trained model;
        history: a log of loss, accuracy and auc_roc
    """

    tf.keras.backend.clear_session()  # For easy reset of notebook state.

    # this could also be the output a different Keras model or layer
    input_tensor = Input(shape=(96, 96, 3)) 

    # create the base pre-trained model
    if model == 'InceptionResNetV2':
        base_model = InceptionResNetV2(input_tensor=input_tensor, weights='imagenet', include_top=False)
    elif model == 'Xception':
        base_model = Xception(input_tensor=input_tensor, weights='imagenet', include_top=False)
    elif model == 'DenseNet':
        base_model = DenseNet201(input_tensor=input_tensor, weights='imagenet', include_top=False)
    elif model == 'NASNet':
        base_model = NASNetLarge(input_tensor=input_tensor, weights='imagenet', include_top=False)
    elif model == 'InceptionV3':  
        base_model = InceptionV3(input_tensor=input_tensor, weights='imagenet', include_top=False)
    elif model == 'ResNet50':  # cannot use imagenet weights as some conv window size changes from (7, 7) to (3, 3)
        base_model = ResNet50(input_tensor=input_tensor, weights=None, include_top=False)    
    elif model == 'small VGGNet':
        base_model = binarySmallerVGGNet.build()
    elif model == 'small CNN':
        base_model = smallCNN.build()
    else:
        print('Please choose a CNN model')


    # add a global spatial average pooling layer
    x = base_model.output

    x = GlobalAveragePooling2D()(x)
    # let's add 2 fully-connected layer
    x = Dense(1024, activation='relu')(x)
    x = Dropout(0.5)(x)
    x = Dense(128, activation='relu')(x)
    # and a logistic layer for binary classes
    predictions = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)

    # this is the model we will train
    model = Model(inputs=base_model.input, outputs=predictions)

    # train the network from scrach
    # i.e. unfreeze all convolutional InceptionV3 layers
    if frozen:
        for layer in base_model.layers:
            layer.trainable = False
        print('all layers frozen')
    else:
        for layer in base_model.layers:
            layer.trainable = True
        print('all layers unfrozen')

    print("[INFO] compiling model...")
    # compile the model
    adam = optimizers.Adam(lr=init_lr)
    model.compile(optimizer=adam, loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

    # print(model.summary())

    # generate augmented data
    train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
                  preprocessing_function=lambda x: x/255.,
                  width_shift_range=4,  # randomly shift images horizontally
                  height_shift_range=4,  # randomly shift images vertically 
                  horizontal_flip=True,  # randomly flip images horizontally
                  vertical_flip=True,  # randomly flip images vertically
                  rotation_range=45)  # randomly rotate images
    
    # this is the augmentation configuration we will use for testing:
    # only rescaling
    valid_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(preprocessing_function=lambda x: x/255.)
    valid_generator = valid_datagen.flow(x_valid, y_valid, batch_size=batch_size)

    # create a callback to save the model weights after each epoch if the validation loss decreased
    file_path = save_model_path
    history = LossHistory()
    callback = [auc_roc_callback(training_data=(x_train, y_train),validation_data=(x_valid, y_valid)),
                ModelCheckpoint(filepath=file_path, monitor='val_auc_roc', mode='max', verbose=1, save_best_only=True),
                history]
#     callback = [ModelCheckpoint(filepath=file_path, monitor='val_loss', verbose=1, save_best_only=True),
#                history]
    
    print("[INFO] training network...")
    start_time = time.time()
    if not subsets:
        train_genearator = train_datagen.flow(x_train, y_train, batch_size=batch_size)
        H = model.fit_generator(train_genearator,
                                steps_per_epoch=len(x_train) // batch_size,
                                validation_data=valid_generator,
                                validation_steps=len(x_valid)//batch_size,
                                epochs=epochs,
                                verbose=1,
                                callbacks=callback)   
    else:
        # divide the train data to 0 subsets and train sequentially due to memory constrains
        start = [i for i in range(0, len(x_train), 10000)]
        end = [i for i in range(10000, len(x_train), 10000)] + [len(x_train)]
        history = []

        for i, j in zip(start, end):
            print('...start train {}/26...'.format(i/10000))
            train_genearator = train_datagen.flow(x_train[i:j], y_train[i:j], batch_size=batch_size)
            H = model.fit_generator(train_genearator,
                                steps_per_epoch=len(x_train[i:j]) // batch_size,
                                validation_data=valid_generator,
                                validation_steps=len(x_valid)//batch_size,
                                epochs=epochs,
                                verbose=1,
                                callbacks=callback               
                            )
    print("finished in {} hours".format((time.time() - start_time)/3600))
    
    return model, H, history

# function to evaluate test data

def evaluate_test(model):
    """
    Args:
        model: a trained CNN model;
    Return:
        loss: cross-entropy loss;
        accuracy: accuracy:
        auc_roc: auc.
    """    
    print("[INFO] evaluating test data...")
    loss, accuracy = model.evaluate(x_test/255., y_test)
    y_pred = model.predict(x_test/255.)
    auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred)
  
    return loss, accuracy, auc

Create a matrix of $96\times96$ patches¶

In [22]:
# compress raw image into (2083, 1041)


def compress_image(model, file_path, batch_size=1):
    
    wsi_id = file_path[-14:-11] + file_path[-5:-4]
    wsi_resized_name = 'wsi_resized_' + wsi_id + '.npy'

    try: 
        print('found wsi_resized...')
        wsi_resized = np.load(wsi_resized_name)
    except: 
        print('no wsi_resized found. creating new array...')
        wsi_resized = np.zeros((2083, 1041))
    
    if wsi_resized[2082, 1040] != 0:
        print('compress wsi {} finished'.format(wsi_id))
    else:
        start = np.sum(wsi_resized, axis=1).argmin()

        if start < batch_size*(2083//batch_size):
            for i in range(start, start + batch_size):
                print('starting row {}...'.format(i))
                for j in range(1041):
                    patch = get_patch(file_path, start_position=[i*96+16, j*96+32], dimension=[96, 96], level=0)/255.
                    # use the model to predict the probability of this patch being a cancer cell        
                    _prob = model.predict(patch[np.newaxis, :, :])
#                     import pdb; pdb.set_trace();
                    wsi_resized[i, j] = _prob
                print('finishing row {}...'.format(i))
        else:
            for i in range(start, 2083):
                print('starting row {}...'.format(i))
                for j in range(1041):
                    patch = get_patch(file_path, start_position=[i*96+16, j*96+32], dimension=[96, 96], level=0)/255.
                    # use the model to predict the probability of this patch being a cancer cell        
                    _prob = model.predict(patch[np.newaxis, :, :])
                    wsi_resized[i, j] = _prob
            print('finishing row {}...'.format(i))
        
        np.save(wsi_resized_name, wsi_resized)

"""

utility function to create static tensorflow graph for hyperparameter tuning

"""

 

def create_mlp_graph(n_inputs, n_outputs, n_hidden_layers=3, n_neurons_per_layer=1000, activation_function=tf.nn.relu, initiation_method='xavier_normal',

                 learning_rate=0.001, optimize_method='adam', dropout_rate=0.5):

  """

  Args:

    n_inputs: no of features of raw input data;

    n_outputs: no of outputs of last layer;

    n_hidden_layers: no of hidden layers;

    n_neurons_per_layer: no of neurons per layer;

    activation_function: activation function of hidden layers;

    initiation_method: initialization method of weights of hidden layers;

    learning_rate: learning rate;

    optimize_method: optimization method for gradient descent;

    dropout_rate: dropout rate for hidden layers.

  Return:

    g: a tennsorflow graph;

    loss: operation for loss function;

    accuracy: accuracy;

    training_op: operation for training the model using some optimization method;

    X: placeholder for raw input data;

    y: placeholder for output data;

    y_proba: predicted probability.

  """

  def build_fcc_layers(inputs, n_hidden, var_scope_name, init_method):

     

      with tf.variable_scope(var_scope_name):

       

          hidden_layers = {} # dictionary of hidden layers

          batch_normal_layers = {} # dictionary of batch normalize layers

          batch_act = {} # dictionary of activation layers

          hidden_dropout_layers = {} # dictionary of dropout layers

 

          for i in range(n_hidden_layers):

            if i == 0:

              hidden_layers['1'] = tf.layers.dense(inputs, n_neurons_per_layer, kernel_initializer=init_method, name="hidden_1")

              batch_normal_layers['1'] = tf.layers.batch_normalization(hidden_layers['1'], training=training, momentum=0.9)

              batch_act['1'] = activation_function(batch_normal_layers['1'])

              hidden_dropout_layers['1'] = tf.layers.dropout(batch_act['1'], dropout_rate, training=training)

            else:

              hidden_layers[str(i+1)] = tf.layers.dense(hidden_dropout_layers[str(i)], n_neurons_per_layer,

                                                               kernel_initializer=init_method, name="hidden_{}".format(i+1))

              batch_normal_layers[str(i+1)] = tf.layers.batch_normalization(hidden_layers[str(i+1)], training=training, momentum=0.9)

              batch_act[str(i+1)] = activation_function(batch_normal_layers[str(i+1)])

              hidden_dropout_layers[str(i+1)] = tf.layers.dropout(batch_act[str(i+1)], dropout_rate, training=training)

   

      return hidden_dropout_layers[str(n_hidden_layers)]

 

  g = tf.Graph()

 

  with g.as_default():

    X = tf.placeholder(tf.float32, shape=(None, n_inputs), name="X")

    y = tf.placeholder(tf.float32, shape=(None, n_outputs), name="y")

    training = tf.placeholder_with_default(False, shape=(), name='training')

    alpha = tf.Variable([1., 1., 1., 1., 1.])

   

    if initiation_method == 'xavier_normal':
      init_method = tf.contrib.layers.xavier_initializer(uniform=False)
    elif initiation_method == 'xavier_uniform':
      init_method = tf.contrib.layers.xavier_initializer(uniform=True)
    elif initiation_method == 'he_normal':
      init_method = tf.initializers.he_normal()
    elif initiation_method == 'he_uniform':
      init_method = tf.initializers.he_uniform()
    elif initiation_method == 'random_normal':
      init_method = tf.random_normal_initializer()
    elif initiation_method == 'random_uniform':
      init_method == tf.random_uniform_initializer()
    else:
      init_method = tf.initializers.TruncatedNormal()

    with tf.name_scope("dnn"):

      hidden_output_1 = build_fcc_layers(inputs=X, n_hidden=n_hidden_layers, var_scope_name='hidden_block_1', init_method=init_method)

      inputs_2 = tf.where(X > 1 - 1e-2, X, tf.zeros_like(X))

      hidden_output_2 = build_fcc_layers(inputs=inputs_2, n_hidden=n_hidden_layers, var_scope_name='hidden_block_2', init_method=init_method)

   

      inputs_3 = tf.where(X > 1 - 1e-3, X, tf.zeros_like(X))

      hidden_output_3 = build_fcc_layers(inputs=inputs_3, n_hidden=n_hidden_layers, var_scope_name='hidden_block_3', init_method=init_method)

   

      inputs_4 = tf.where(X > 1 - 1e-4, X, tf.zeros_like(X))

      hidden_output_4 = build_fcc_layers(inputs=inputs_4, n_hidden=n_hidden_layers, var_scope_name='hidden_block_4', init_method=init_method)

   

      inputs_5 = tf.where(X > 1 - 1e-5, X, tf.zeros_like(X))

      hidden_output_5 = build_fcc_layers(inputs=inputs_5, n_hidden=n_hidden_layers, var_scope_name='hidden_block_5', init_method=init_method)

       

        

#       hidden_outputs_stack = tf.stack([hidden_output_1, hidden_output_2, hidden_output_3,

#                                        hidden_output_4, hidden_output_5])   

#       hidden_output = tf.reshape(tf.matmul(tf.reshape(alpha, (1, 5)), tf.reshape(hidden_outputs_stack, (5, -1))),

#                                  (-1, 1000))

     

      hidden_output = alpha[0]*hidden_output_1 + alpha[1]*hidden_output_2 + alpha[2]*hidden_output_3 + \
                        alpha[3]*hidden_output_4 + alpha[4]*hidden_output_5

     

      logits = tf.layers.dense(hidden_output, n_outputs, activation=tf.nn.relu, kernel_initializer=init_method,

                             name="last")

 

    with tf.name_scope("loss"):

      xentropy = tf.nn.sigmoid_cross_entropy_with_logits(labels=y,logits=logits)

      loss = tf.reduce_mean(xentropy)

       

      y_proba = tf.nn.sigmoid(logits)  # prediction

      correct = tf.equal(tf.round(y_proba), y)

      accuracy = tf.reduce_mean(tf.cast(correct, tf.float32))

 

    with tf.name_scope("train"):

      if optimize_method == 'nesterov': # nesterov optimizer

        optimizer = tf.train.MomentumOptimizer(learning_rate=learning_rate, momentum=0.9, use_nesterov=True)

      elif optimize_method == 'adam': # adam optimizer

        optimizer = tf.train.AdamOptimizer(learning_rate=learning_rate)

      else: # momentum optimizer

        optimizer = tf.train.MomentumOptimizer(learning_rate=learning_rate, momentum=0.9)

      training_op = optimizer.minimize(loss)

 

  return g, loss, accuracy, training_op, X, y, y_proba, logits

"""

utility function to create static tensorflow graph for hyperparameter tuning

"""

 

def create_cnn_graph(n_inputs,

                 height,

                 width,

                 channels,

                 n_outputs,

                 conv_layers_hp=[{'kernel':32, 'ksize':[1, 3], 'stride':[1, 1], 'padding':'SAME'},

                                 {'kernel':64, 'ksize':[1, 3], 'stride':[1, 1], 'padding':'SAME'}],

                 pool_layers_hp=[{'ksize':[1, 1], 'stride':[1, 2], 'padding':'VALID'},

                                 {'ksize':[1, 1], 'stride':[1, 1], 'padding':'VALID'}],

                 pool_dropout_rate = 0.5,

                 fc_layers_hp=1024,

                 fc_dropout_rate = 0.5,

                 learning_rate=0.001,

                 average_pool=False):

  """

  Args:

    n_inputs: no of features of raw input data;

    height, width, channelsdimension of a single instance of X;

    n_outputs: no of outputs of last layer;

    conv_layers_hp: list of dictionary of hyperparameters of convalutional layers.

                    length of conv_layers has to be the same as pool_layer_hp;

    pool_layers_hp: list of dictionary of hyperparameters of max_pool layers.

                    length of pool_layers has to be the same as conv_layer_hp;

    pool_dropout_rate: dropout rate after the final pool layer;

    fc_layers_hp: no of neurons of every fully connected layers;

    fc_dropout_rate: dropout rate after the fully connected layer;

    learning_rate: learning rate;

    average_pool: True if average_pooling used before the last layer else False.

  Return:

    g: a tennsorflow graph

    loss: operation for loss function

    training_op: operation for training the model using some optimization method

    X: placeholder for raw input data;

    y: placeholder for output data.

  """

 

  def build_cnn_layers(inputs, n_blocks, var_scope_name):

     

      with tf.variable_scope(var_scope_name):

          conv_layers = {} # dictionary of conv layers

          pool_layers = {} # dictionary of max_pool layers

 

          for i in range(n_blocks):

            if i == 0:

              conv_layers['1'] = tf.layers.conv2d(inputs,

                                              filters=conv_layers_hp[0]['kernel'],

                                              kernel_size=conv_layers_hp[0]['ksize'],

                                              strides=conv_layers_hp[0]['stride'],

                                              padding=conv_layers_hp[0]['padding'],

                                              activation=tf.nn.relu, name="conv_1")

              pool_layers['1'] = tf.nn.max_pool(conv_layers['1'],

                                                ksize= [1] + pool_layers_hp[0]['ksize'] + [1],

                                                strides= [1] + pool_layers_hp[0]['stride'] + [1],

                                                padding= pool_layers_hp[0]['padding'], name='pool_1')

            else:

              conv_layers[str(i+1)] = tf.layers.conv2d(pool_layers[str(i)],  

                                                   filters=conv_layers_hp[i]['kernel'],                                       

                                                   kernel_size=conv_layers_hp[i]['ksize'],

                                                   strides=conv_layers_hp[i]['stride'],

                                                   padding=conv_layers_hp[i]['padding'],

                                                   activation=tf.nn.relu, name="conv_{}".format(i+1))

              pool_layers[str(i+1)] = tf.nn.max_pool(conv_layers[str(i+1)], ksize= [1] + pool_layers_hp[i]['ksize'] + [1],

                                               strides= [1] + pool_layers_hp[i]['stride'] + [1],  

                                               padding= pool_layers_hp[i]['padding'], name='pool_{}'.format(i+1))

 

 

                # convert multi-channel to one channel by flattening

          if average_pool: # if average-pooling is used, no extra fully-connected layer is created

            ave_pool_layer = tf.reduce_mean(pool_layers[str(n_blocks)], axis=[1,2])  # average the whole channel for every channel

            feature_dim = ave_pool_layer.shape[1]  # flatten the multi-channel to 1 channel

            ave_pool_flatten = tf.reshape(ave_pool_layer, [-1, feature_dim]) # fully connected layer

            fc = tf.layers.dense(ave_pool_flatten, fc_layers_hp, activation=tf.nn.relu, name="fc")  # fully connected layer

          else:  # if average-pooling is not used, a fully-connected layer is created after last pool layer and before last layer

            feature_dim = pool_layers[str(n_blocks)].shape[1] * pool_layers[str(n_blocks)].shape[2] * pool_layers[str(n_blocks)].shape[3] 

            pool_flat = tf.reshape(pool_layers[str(n_blocks)], [-1, feature_dim])  # flatten the multi-channels to 1 channel

            pool_flat_drop = tf.layers.dropout(pool_flat, pool_dropout_rate, training=training)

            fc = tf.layers.dense(pool_flat_drop, fc_layers_hp, activation=tf.nn.relu, name="fc")  # fully connected layer

 

          fc_drop = tf.layers.dropout(fc, fc_dropout_rate, training=training) 

        

      return fc_drop

       

        

  g = tf.Graph()

 

  with g.as_default():

    X = tf.placeholder(tf.float32, shape=(None, n_inputs), name="X")

    X_reshaped = tf.reshape(X, shape=[-1, height, width, channels])

    y = tf.placeholder(tf.float32, shape=(None, n_outputs), name="y")

    training = tf.placeholder_with_default(False, shape=(), name='training')

    alpha = tf.Variable([1., 1., 1., 1., 1.])

 

    # check if we have the same no of conv_layers and pool_layers

    assert len(conv_layers_hp) == len(pool_layers_hp), 'conv_layers and pool_layers should have the same length'

 

    # no of blocks of conv_layer + pool_layer

    n_blocks = len(conv_layers_hp)

 

    with tf.name_scope("dnn"):

      hidden_output_1 = build_cnn_layers(X_reshaped, n_blocks=n_blocks, var_scope_name='hidden_block_1')

   

      inputs_2 = tf.where(X_reshaped > 1 - 1e-2, X_reshaped, tf.zeros_like(X_reshaped))

      hidden_output_2 = build_cnn_layers(inputs=inputs_2, n_blocks=n_blocks, var_scope_name='hidden_block_2')

   

      inputs_3 = tf.where(X_reshaped > 1 - 1e-3, X_reshaped, tf.zeros_like(X_reshaped))

      hidden_output_3 = build_cnn_layers(inputs=inputs_3, n_blocks=n_blocks, var_scope_name='hidden_block_3')

   

      inputs_4 = tf.where(X_reshaped > 1 - 1e-4, X_reshaped, tf.zeros_like(X_reshaped))

      hidden_output_4 = build_cnn_layers(inputs=inputs_4, n_blocks=n_blocks, var_scope_name='hidden_block_4')

   

      inputs_5 = tf.where(X_reshaped > 1 - 1e-5, X_reshaped, tf.zeros_like(X_reshaped))

      hidden_output_5 = build_cnn_layers(inputs=inputs_5, n_blocks=n_blocks, var_scope_name='hidden_block_5')

       

        

#       hidden_outputs_stack = tf.stack([hidden_output_1, hidden_output_2, hidden_output_3,

#                                        hidden_output_4, hidden_output_5])   

#       hidden_output = tf.reshape(tf.matmul(tf.reshape(alpha, (1, 5)), tf.reshape(hidden_outputs_stack, (5, -1))),

#                                  (-1, 1000))

     

      hidden_output = alpha[0]*hidden_output_1 + alpha[1]*hidden_output_2 + alpha[2]*hidden_output_3 + \
                        alpha[3]*hidden_output_4 + alpha[4]*hidden_output_5

     

      logits = tf.layers.dense(hidden_output, n_outputs, activation=tf.nn.relu,

                               kernel_initializer=tf.contrib.layers.xavier_initializer(),

                               name="last") 

 

    with tf.name_scope("loss"):

      xentropy = tf.nn.sigmoid_cross_entropy_with_logits(labels=y,logits=logits)

      loss = tf.reduce_mean(xentropy)

       

      y_proba = tf.nn.sigmoid(logits)  # prediction

      correct = tf.equal(tf.round(y_proba), y)

      accuracy = tf.reduce_mean(tf.cast(correct, tf.float32))

 

    with tf.name_scope("train"):

      optimizer = tf.train.AdamOptimizer(learning_rate=learning_rate)

      training_op = optimizer.minimize(loss)

 

  return g, loss, accuracy, training_op, X, y, y_proba
